p: Between the time periods 2006–2010 and 2011–2015, HIV diagnosis rates attributed to male-to-male sex increased 1.37 times (95% CI 1.14–1.65) in men born in South-East Asia, 2.18 times (95% CI 1.64–2.89) in men born in North-East Asia and 1.37 times (95% CI 1.04–1.79) for men from the Americas, as expressed by the SRR. Changes for other regions of birth were not significant.
